cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the social network structure and dynamics of Twitter. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper may discuss the software tools and methods used to collect and analyze the Twitter data. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper investigates patterns of sentiment expression and the effect of network topology on happiness. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the natural language processing techniques used to analyze the sentiment of Twitter messages. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the societal implications of the findings on Twitter social networks and sentiment expression.
